The paper discusses the study of sociotechnical systems, which involves the intersection of computer science and social science. The paper specifically focuses on social networks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). The paper also touches on issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), as well as organization theory (cs.CE) and ecology (cs.CR).
